trans-unit.source: Binds a <xref href="System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand"></xref> to the event handlers that implement the command.
trans-unit.target: Binding en <xref href="System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand"> </xref> til hendelsesbehandlingen som implementerer kommandoen.

trans-unit.source: A CommandBinding associates a command with the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewExecuted>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.Executed> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewCanExecute>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.CanExecute> events which implement and determine the status of the command.
trans-unit.target: En CommandBinding knytter en kommando med den <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewExecuted>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.Executed> og <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewCanExecute>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.CanExecute> hendelser som implementerer og fastslå statusen for kommandoen.</xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.CanExecute> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewCanExecute> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.Executed> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewExecuted>

trans-unit.source: When the <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.Execute%2A> or <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.CanExecute%2A> method of a <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> is called, the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewExecuted>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.Executed> or the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewCanExecute>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.CanExecute> events are raised on the command target.
trans-unit.target: Når den <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.Execute%2A>eller <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.CanExecute%2A>-metoden til et <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>kalles, den <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewExecuted>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.Executed> eller <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewCanExecute>/<xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.CanExecute> hendelser registreres i kommandoen måldatabasen.</xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.CanExecute> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewCanExecute> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.Executed> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandBinding.PreviewExecuted> </xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> </xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.CanExecute%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.Execute%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the command target has a CommandBinding for the command, the appropriate handlers are called.
trans-unit.target: Hvis kommandoen målet har en CommandBinding for kommandoen, er riktig behandlingsprogramdelen kalles.

trans-unit.source: If the command target does not have a CommandBinding for the command, the events are routed through the element tree until an element that has a CommandBinding is found.
trans-unit.target: Hvis målet kommandoen ikke har en CommandBinding for kommandoen, rutes hendelsene gjennom treet elementet til et element som har en CommandBinding blir funnet.

trans-unit.source: A CommandBinding has limited use with an <xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand> that is not a<xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>.
trans-unit.target: En CommandBinding er begrenset til bruk med en <xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand>som er ikke en<xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>.</xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ICommand>

trans-unit.source: This is because a CommandBinding binds the command to the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ExecutedRoutedEventHandler> and the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CanExecuteRoutedEventHandler> which listen to the <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandManager.Executed> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandManager.CanExecute> routed events which are raised when the <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.Execute%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.CanExecute%2A> method of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> are called.
trans-unit.target: Fordi en CommandBinding binding kommandoen til den <xref:System.Windows.Input.ExecutedRoutedEventHandler>og <xref:System.Windows.Input.CanExecuteRoutedEventHandler>som lytte til den <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandManager.Executed>og <xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandManager.CanExecute>rutet hendelser som aktiveres når den <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.Execute%2A>og <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.CanExecute%2A>-metoden til den <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>kalles.</xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> </xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.CanExecute%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand.Execute%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandManager.CanExecute> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CommandManager.Executed> </xref:System.Windows.Input.CanExecuteRoutedEventHandler> </xref:System.Windows.Input.ExecutedRoutedEventHandler>
